The paper discusses the possibility of training a machine to detect if another machine has understood a concept, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques to achieve this goal. Additionally, the paper touches upon the metaphysical implications of understanding and meaning, which could potentially fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
